# m5_p16_foundry_full.shot — M5 P16
#
# Verifies the Foundry map kit (parallax + tile assets) end-to-end:
#   - parallax_far drawn behind world (orange clouds on dark sky)
#   - parallax_mid + parallax_near drawn as additional background layers
#     (M6 P10 2026-05-16 — near layer moved pre-world; the shipped foundry
#     parallax_near.png is a dense opaque factory silhouette, not edge
#     art, so painting it post-world was hiding the playable geometry)
#   - halftone post-process screen over the whole frame
#   - Trooper chassis sprite + Pulse Rifle held in R_HAND
#   - HUD: HP bar, jet bar, armor pip, crosshair, ammo text, weapon labels
#
# Use m5_p16_chassis_lineup.shot for the 5-chassis-on-tutorial sprite
# verification — at the Foundry's 1.4x camera zoom only ~914 px of world
# is visible per frame, which can't fit a 5-chassis lineup. This shot
# is the "look at one chassis with parallax behind it" check.
#
# Run:
#   ./soldut --shot tests/shots/m5_p16_foundry_full.shot
# Output:
#   build/shots/m5_p16_foundry_full/full.png
#   build/shots/m5_p16_foundry_full/m5_p16_foundry_full.log
#
# Verification:
#   - the log shows `map_kit: loaded N/4 textures for 'foundry'` with
#     N >= 3 (parallax_far/mid/near; tiles.png is optional)
#   - the log shows `mech_sprites: loaded` for trooper.png (no
#     "renders as capsules" lines)
#   - the log shows `halftone: shader loaded` + `hud: atlas loaded`
#   - the rendered PNG shows orange clouds (parallax_far), industrial
#     silhouettes layered over them (parallax_mid + near), the Trooper
#     standing on the spawn platform holding a rifle, and the HUD

window 1280 720
seed   42 7
out    build/shots/m5_p16_foundry_full

# Foundry is a 100x40-tile map (3200x1280 px). Spawn platform sits at
# row 30 (top y = 960). Place the player on the platform.
map foundry
loadout Trooper "Pulse Rifle" "Frag Grenades" Light Standard

# Player centered in the visible viewport — camera follows him.
spawn_at 600 920
mouse    900 350

# Let physics settle the pose, then capture once.
at  90 shot full
at 120 end
